                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 161.) On the 29th of Dec., about five o'clock, I saw the prisoner coming out of Carr-square—she had this bundle in her arms—I apprehended her.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I met a woman; she asked me to carry the bundle for her to Union-street, and she would give me sixpence; the policeman stopped me, and asked where I got the things; I told him.</p>
